he `/api/v1/documents/route.ts` endpoint. I've decided on case-insensitive comparisons for `document_type`, `status`, and `visibility`. For the search functionality, I will be conducting case-insensitive checks on the `title`, `description`, `owner`, and `id` fields.\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm starting to design the `POST` endpoint for creating documents. Currently, I've confirmed that only admin roles should have the authority to create them. I've worked out the response if non-admin roles try to create one, returning a 403. Also, I've outlined that the required fields for creation are `title` and either `document_type` or `type`. I've added `status` to be optional.\n\n\n**Validating Document Fields**\n\nI'm now focusing on validating the fields for document creation via the `POST` endpoint. I've begun to validate fields like `client_id`, checking it against a list of valid IDs (\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\") and returning a 400 if it's invalid. I'm leveraging `getClientNameFromId()` to retrieve the `client_name`. I also plan to use `getNextDocumentId()` and create a mock SHA256 if needed.\n\n\n**Defining Default Values**\n\nI'm now focusing on setting default values. I've noted that if a `sha256` hash is missing from the request body, I can create one using a random byte sequence and formatting it as a hex string. For `fileSize`, I've set \"1.5 MB\" as the default, unless overridden. I'm checking if `governanceChecks` is provided in the request body, defaulting to an empty array if missing. I'm ensuring consistency with the expected JSON response.\n\n\n**Designing Document Detail Routes**\n\nI'm now structuring the `GET` and `PATCH` endpoints within `app/api/v1/documents/[id]/route.ts`. For `GET`, I'll return a 404 if the document is missing. I have to check the caller's role, and if it is not an admin, then I must perform extra checks. I'm ensuring non-admin callers can only access their client's documents and that internal-only visibility documents return a 403 Forbidden error. For the `PATCH` endpoint, non-admins should receive a 403. Also, I must ensure `document_type` and `type` remain synchronized.\n\n\n"}}
