{"ts":"2026-06-27T16:24:23.115Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying Route Availability**\n\nI've confirmed a critical gap: no existing Python FastAPI endpoint handles documents. My focus shifted to verifying this endpoint absence, expanding the investigation to encompass potential alternative routes or API endpoints within the current Next.js architecture. The conclusion? The work leans toward implementing Next.js App Router API endpoints for documents.\n\n\n**Confirming Documentation API**\n\nI'm now certain about the implementation path: the Next.js routes under `app/api/v1/documents` are the correct target. I've noted existing, partially-written route files and UI dependencies, which strongly support this direction. Additionally, I'll be creating a complementary testing script, patterned after `test-governance-apis.js`, to ensure thorough API validation. Before coding, I will create a design plan as the prompt requests.\n\n\n**Defining API Metadata Design**\n\nI've sketched out the crucial design concepts. I am focused on a high-security document metadata registry. I envision a system accessible to admins and clients, emphasizing zero-trust security and HSM-signed attestation. I am considering a cryptographic ledger metaphor with clear JSON/REST schemas. I've started layout with standard RESTful routes under Next.js App Router for CRUD operations.\n\n\n**Designing API Interactions**\n\nI've detailed the specifics of the planned API interactions. I'm focusing on securing the `GET`, `PATCH`, and `DELETE` methods for the `/api/v1/documents/[id]` route, enforcing strict client-boundary isolation. I am considering default metadata like custom IDs, mock SHA-256 hashes, sizes, and commits to memory. All interactions will require a valid Bearer token, representing a signed GFF JWT to manage authentication and role-based access control.\n\n\n**Implementing API Functions**\n\nI'm now focused on the concrete implementation steps. My first actions involve modifying `lib/api-auth.ts`, specifically adding a `getNextDocumentId()` helper and refining the `ApiDocumentItem` interface. I'm prioritizing the completion of the `GET` list and `POST` create methods in `app/api/v1/documents/route.ts`. Simultaneously, I'll complete `GET` single, `PATCH`, and `DELETE` in `app/api/v1/documents/[id]/route.ts`. Finally, I'll verify the existing build and lint and create `/scripts/test-document-apis.js`.\n\n\n**Refining Data Structures**\n\nI'm updating the `ApiDocumentItem` interface. I'm adding `document_type`, `project_id`, and `visibility` fields to accommodate the explicit requirements, and adapting the existing `type` and `projectId` for backward compatibility. I plan to use these new fields in the `GET`, `POST`, `PATCH`, and `DELETE` requests for `/api/v1/documents`.\n\n\n"}}
