{"ts":"2026-06-27T16:29:19.917Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"3wj0mg7b","input":{"summary":"### GFF AI Sovereign Document Metadata CRUD APIs Implementation Summary\n\nI have fully built and integrated the Documents metadata CRUD APIs under `/api/v1/documents` in accordance with the Phase 5 Portal Admin API specs and UI Quality Constitution.\n\n#### 1. Page & API Architectural Narrative\nThe document registry serves as a high-security cryptographic metadata store. The API facilitates metadata management with full tenant isolation, RBAC enforcement, and visibility tier controls.\n\n#### 2. Key Components & Implementation\n- **`/lib/api-auth.ts`**:\n  - Updated `ApiDocumentItem` to explicitly support the requested metadata fields: `document_type`, `project_id`, and `visibility`.\n  - Back-compatibility is preserved by keeping `type` and `projectId` in sync with the new fields.\n  - Added new mock documents representing actual production-ready metadata.\n  - Implemented the `getNextDocumentId()` helper to automatically generate the next unique cryptographic document ID (e.g., `DOC-805`, `DOC-806`, etc.).\n\n- **`/app/api/v1/documents/route.ts`**:\n  - **`GET`**: Enhanced filter mechanisms supporting `client_id`, `project_id` (or `projectId`), `document_type` (or `type`), `status`, `visibility`, and query-based `search`. Implemented visibility rules where non-admins (client roles) are blocked from accessing sovereign-only, internal-use, or strictly confidential documents. Client roles are strictly isolated within their own tenant boundary.\n  - **`POST`**: Added metadata creation, validating required fields (`title` and `client_id`), assigning a new unique ID, generating simulated cryptographic hashes (SHA-256), and saving the record to the mock database. Restriced to `gff_admin` users (returns `403 Forbidden` for client roles).\n\n- **`/app/api/v1/documents/[id]/route.ts`**:\n  - **`GET`**: Returns detailed single document metadata, checking tenant isolation boundaries and visibility constraints.\n  - **`PATCH`**: Permits admins (`gff_admin`) to update document metadata fields (like title, description, status, version, owner, project, type, visibility, and governance checks), updating the `lastUpdated` timestamp dynamically. Restriced to `gff_admin` users (returns `403 Forbidden` for client roles).\n  - **`DELETE`**: Permits admins to completely purge/archive metadata from the HSM registry. Restriced to `gff_admin` users (returns `403 Forbidden` for client roles).\n\n- **`/scripts/test-document-apis.js`**:\n  - Created a custom integration test script mimicking other API test frameworks. It compiles the route files with `tsc` and runs complete end-to-end tests for all CRUD operations, filters, tenant boundaries, inactive-user checks, and admin-only restriction policies.\n\n#### 3. Validation Completed\n- Successfully executed end-to-end integration tests using the newly created script. Output confirmed: `✔ VERIFICATION SUCCESSFUL: Documents CRUD APIs Verified!`.\n- Ran `npx tsc --noEmit` and confirmed that all TypeScript checks compiled successfully with zero type or configuration errors.\n- Verified that existing front-end portal pages fetch properly from `/api/v1/documents` and work seamlessly with the new schema.\n","verified":true}}}
